# GitHub Pages user guide — sync before push

When the user asks to **`git commit`**, **`git push`**, or ship to the repo, refresh the public user guide **`docs/`** (MkDocs) **before** staging — same gate as Xcode preflight and changelog sync. Updated guide pages ship in **the same commit** as app changes.

## Source of truth

Compare **`docs/`** against:

1. **`GoDiveMVP/cursor/app_summary.md`** — user-visible behavior and flows  
2. The **latest open** section of **`GoDiveMVP/cursor/change_log.md`** — what is shipping in this batch  
3. Code when summary/changelog are stale

**Do not** mirror the change log on Pages. Pages describe **how the app works now**, in plain language for divers.

## Update when

- New or removed **screens, tabs, or navigation** paths  
- Changed **user workflows** (import, search, tagging, trips, settings toggles)  
- New/changed **data rules** users see (units, renumber, duplicates, permissions)  
- New **features** or **behavior fixes** that change what users can do or expect  
- Renamed labels or settings that appear in the guide  

## Skip (usually no doc edit)

- Visual polish (colors, glass, scrims, spacing, animations)  
- Performance, caching, or launch-time optimizations  
- Internal refactors with **no** user-visible behavior change  
- Agent/cursor rules, test-only changes, developer architecture notes  
- Screenshot updates (user adds those separately unless a flow moved)

When unsure: if a new user would misunderstand the app without an edit, update **`docs/`**; if not, skip.

## How to edit

- **`docs/*.md`** — user-facing pages only; no file paths or Swift identifiers unless essential  
- **`mkdocs.yml`** — nav when adding/removing/renaming pages  
- Tone: short sections, tables/lists where helpful; match existing guide style  
- Do **not** add release-note sections or “what changed in §NN” prose  

## Push workflow order

1. Finish app + **`change_log.md`** / **`app_summary.md`** work  
2. **Sync `docs/`** per this rule (this step)  
3. iPhone 17 sim preflight (**`xcode-test-only-when-asked.mdc`**)  
4. **`git commit`** — include **`docs/`** / **`mkdocs.yml`** when touched  
5. **`git push`** when requested  

## Handoff

Do **not** push while user-facing behavior in the batch is **missing or wrong** in **`docs/`**. If nothing functional changed, say so briefly — no filler edits.
